File: Donny van de Beek at the Johan Cruyff Arena in Amsterdam, on August 8, 2020. LONDON - Manchester United on Wednesday announced the signing of Ajax midfielder Donny van de Beek for a reported fee of £34 million ($45 million) plus add-ons. READ: Messi's father lands in Spain as Barca stand-off drags on Ole Gunnar Solskjaer made the 23-year-old midfielder his first signing of the summer transfer window. Van de Beek played an important role in Ajax's run to last year's Champions League semi-finals and has signed a five-year deal at Old Trafford with the option of a further season.